==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[geara|ġēara]] + [[dæg|dæġ]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'jæ:aɹˌdaɣas/

===Noun===
'''ġēardagas''' ''m pl''
# days of old, days of yore
#:''An man wæs on geardagum eardiende on þam iglande þe Creta hatte'': one man in days of old lived on the island called Crete.  (Wulfstan, ''De falsis deis'')

